OL,4,Cresuscitate' notice of the wrong
OL,5,Cpatient
OL,7,FThe inquest heard that staff had
OL,8,Ffailed to check the NHS number on
OL,9,FPat's wristband or even by confirming
OL,10,Fthe gender and age on the notes.
OL,11,FGiving evidence to the inquest,
OL,12,Femergency consultant Dr Ahmad Alabood
OL,13,Fsaid it had been an 'honest mistake
OL,14,Fbecause (staff) were rushing'.
OL,16,FDr Alabood said that, when Pat was
OL,17,Fbrought into A&E, the department was
OL,18,F'significantly over-stretched and over-
OL,19,Fcrowded'. All eight bays in resus were
OL,20,Ffull and each nurse had an unlimited
OL,21,Fnumber of patients to look after.
