OL,5,Cpatient
OL,7,FA post mortem CT scan confirmed the
OL,8,Fcause of Pat's death was aspiration
OL,9,Fpneumonitis after she inhaled stomach
OL,10,Fcontents. This was caused by a small
OL,11,Fbowel obstruction.
OL,13,FReturning a narrative conclusion, the
OL,14,Fcoroner flagged up several areas of
OL,15,Fsub-standard care' which Pat had
OL,16,Freceived including a failure to record
OL,17,Fany of the tests carried out in
OL,18,Fhospital, not following the sepsis and
OL,19,Fabdominal pathways and the error in
OL,20,Fchecking the wrong patient's notes.
